summary: This document provides information on how to view aircraft records, detailing the types of files included on a CD Rom, the format of the documents, and the sequence in which they are displayed. It also explains the various document types related to aircraft records and their contents.
keyFacts: The document outlines the structure and content of aircraft records available on CD Rom.
It describes the types of files included, such as Airworthiness, Registration, and Suspense files.
The document explains how to navigate and view the records using Adobe Acrobat Reader.
